'''Enterovirus C''' is a species of enterovirus. Its best known subtype is [[poliovirus]], the cause of [[poliomyelitis]].<ref>{{cite web |publisher=International Committee on Taxonomy of Viruses |title=ICTV 2009 Master Species List Version 10 |date=August 2011 |url=http://talk.ictvonline.org/files/ictv_documents/m/msl/1231.aspx}}</ref> There are three [[serotype]]s of poliovirus, PV1, PV2, and PV3. Other subtypes of Enterovirus C include EV-C95, EV-C96, EV-C99, EV-C102, EV-C104, EV-C105, EV-C109, EV-C116, EV-C117, and EV-C118. Several of these can cause the [[polio-like condition]] AFP ([[acute flaccid paralysis]]).

