{{short description|A Dutch oceanographic expedition in the waters of eastern Indonesia.}}
{{Orphan|date=June 2014}}

The '''Snellius Expedition''' was an  [[oceanography]] expedition organized by the Dutch with emphasis on the fields of geology and oceanography in the waters of eastern [[Indonesia]].<ref name="a">{{id}} Shaadily, Hassan. ''Ensiklopedia Indonesia Jilid 3''. Jakarta: Ichtiar Baru dan Van Hoeve.</ref> This expedition is famous as the largest oceanological expedition ever undertaken in these waters.<ref name="a"/> The expedition was conducted by the [[Netherlands|Dutch]] navy ship, named [[HNMS Willebrord Snell]], named after the Dutch mathematician, [[Willebrord Snellius|Willebrord Snell]].<ref name="a"/> The expedition was led by [[Dr. P.M. van Riel]] and the sea voyage led by [[Lieutenant F. Pinke]].<ref name="a"/> This study took place from July 27, 1929 until [[25 November 1930]].<ref name="a"/>

